<tr>
  <td BGCOLOR="#CCCCFF" colspan=2><center>
  <h2>Ontology Widget</h2></center><p>
  The ontology widget and supporting service is a user interface 
  tool for browsing ontology data.
  <br><br>
  The current version of the Ontology Widget Proxy  1.1 and was  <i> updated September 17 2008. </i> 
  <p>
  This version is working on Firefox, Opera, and Safari on the Mac and <br>
                                  Firefox, Opera, and IE on XP.  <p>
  </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
  <td BGCOLOR="whitesmoke">
  <p><br>
  The Ontology Widget Proxy is a proxy servlet for installation on 
  your site. <a  href=OntologyWidgetProxy.war > Download the .war file </a>
 <br> The source code for the proxy servlet may be downloaded as a  <a href=owp.tar.gz> gzipped archive</a>.
 
 <p><br>
  New in this version is an example.jsp that obviates the need to edit a static html page before deploying the webapp.<br>
  There are also new versions of the javascript files used by the proxy servlet. These are linked from the example.jsp. 

  <p><br>
  Documentation is available for <a href=http://smd.stanford.edu/ontologyWidget/OntologyBrowserHelp.doc>   download </a> or browsing 
  <a href=http://smd.stanford.edu/ontologyWidget/OntologyWidgetHelp.htm> online.
  </a> 
  <p><br>
  Click
  <a  href=http://smd.stanford.edu/js/ontology/v1/ExampleProduction.html>here</a>
  to test drive the widget with live ontology data.

  </td>
  </tr>
</table>
